OL,5, For the first time fewer than half of  
OL,6, people in England and Wales describe   
OL,7, themselves as Christian, the Census    
OL,8, 2021 has revealed.                     
OL,10,FThe proportion of people who said they 
OL,11,Fwere Christian was 46.2%, down from    
OL,12,F59.3% in the last census in 2011.      
OL,14,FIn contrast the number who said they   
OL,15,Fhad no religion increased to 37.2% of  
OL,16,Fthe population, up from a quarter.     
OL,18,FThose identifying as Muslim rose from  
OL,19,F4.9% in 2011 to 6.5% last year.        
